<br>
Case in point- slaves in classic Rome were paid, given good room and board, and generally had an okay time of it save being at the complete and total beck and call of their masters.  On the other hand, we have the slaves of antebellum USA.  Then we also have current slavery that goes on in various parts of the world today (sex slaves n what not).<br>
<br>
Given the current United States outlook, I wouldn't want slaves as I value the freedom of my fellow man and woman more than I do having someone to clean my room.  Maid, hells yah.  Slave, naw. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=muglackdackfut>Muglack DackFut</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of Mulletude</span><br>  Posts: 3865<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 10:58:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1341.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Slavery</span><hr size=1> How about a maid that you bought from another person. The Maid/Butler lived in your house, and in exchange for free room and board was charged with the duty of preforming all remedial domestic tasks, and was forever in your service unless you let them go, or sold to someone else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=martif>Martif</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 566<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 11:14:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1341.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> no... no slaves for me.</span><hr size=1> <br>
